===Etymology===
: [[Rohing]] + [[Ya]] meaning ''the people of Rohing''. Rohang is the old kingdom name of [[Arakan]] in present-day [[Myanmar]] (fomerly known as [[Burma]]).

===Proper noun===
'''Rohingya'''

# The [[people]] of [[Arakan]], Myanmar.
# The Indo-European language spoken in [[Arakan]], Myanmar.

